The EO distilled from leaves of L. heteromorpha was a yellowish waxy solid, easily melted at low temperatures. Due to its physical state, it was recovered dissolving it in dichloromethane and the yield of each distillation was determined through semi-quantitative Gas Chromatographic analysis with Flame Ionization Detector (GC-FID). The resulting average yield was 0.06 ± 0.029 % ( w/w), referred to fresh plant material. The detected and quantified components cover 99.1% of the EO; its specific rotatory power was [α
] D 20
= −5.6 (c 5.07 in CH 2Cl 2). The qualitative and semi-quantitative compositions of the EO are reported in Table 1.
